Translation: we [brought [bo]wmen and shieldmen [... into] the king's fort
I prepared everything for the journey of Abu-eriba, the king's relative, and his wife, and they have now arrived. (a-du-ú KASKAL.2 a-na GÌR.2-MEŠ šá AD—eri-ba NUMUN—LUGAL ù DAM-šú ki-i áš-ku-na)
they succeed in turning me out [of the gra]ce of the king!
that they can be sent back!
We fear the king, our lord, and shall never place a woe on them! (ú-a ina ŠÀ-bi-šú-nu ⸢la ni-šak-kan⸣)
Notes: Interesting example: place woe upon them

Translation: on the 16th [of Shebat] I sent the messengers of the ki[ng], my lord, on the road ( KASKAL.2 a-na [GÌR.2-šú-nu] liš-ku-nu-⸢ma⸣)
they succeed in turning me out of the grace of the king, my lord!
the king's name is settled upon them (⸢šu-um⸣ šá LUGAL ina UGU-ḫi-šú-nu šak-[nu x)
